President Biden announced the launch of a new Partnership for Workers' Rights, emphasizing the importance of protecting workers' dignity and respect. The partnership aims to address issues such as forced labor, child labor, worker exploitation, and workplace discrimination. It also focuses on promoting safe and decent work, advancing a worker-centric clean energy transition, harnessing technology for the benefit of workers, and promoting work equality through collective bargaining. President Lula of Brazil expressed his gratitude for the partnership and highlighted the need to address poverty, discrimination, and the rights of marginalized groups in the labor market. The Director-General of the International Labour Organization (ILO) praised the initiative and affirmed the ILO's commitment to advancing social justice and decent work.